parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "SAMtools",
"details": {
"other_software": "gcc",
"modules": ["gcc/6.4.0", "samtools/1.8"],
"resource_requirements": {
"time": "0-02:30",
"partition": "thinnodes",
"cores": 24,
"mail_type": ["TIME_LIMIT_80", "END"],
"mail_user": "enricobazzical@gmail.com"
},
"input": [
"sample name (given as the first command)",
"fastq folder path (given as the second command)"
],
"output": "A csv file containing mapped read statistics with the following columns:
\n\n* **sample_name**: name of the sample
\n* **total_seq**: number of reads in the fastq file
\n* **total_reads**: number of alignments in the BAM file
\n* **duplicates**: marked duplicates
\n* **mapped**: mapped reads
\n* **properly_pair**: pairs of reads properly paired
\n* **with_mat_to_another_chr**: reads with mate mapped to another chromosome
\n* **uniq_mapped**: mapped reads without duplicates
\n* **uniq_mapped_vs_total_reads**: Percentage of unique mapped reads over total reads
\n* **duplicates_vs_total_reads**: Percentage of duplicates over total reads
\n* **MAPPED_vs_TOTAL_SEQ**: Percentage of mapped reads over total reads in fastq
\n* **properly_pair_vs_total_seq**: Percentage of properly paired reads over total reads in fastq
\n* **with_mat_to_another_chr_vs_total_seq**: Percentage of reads with mate mapped to another chromosome over total reads in fastq
\n* **samtools_depth**: Mean depth and standard deviation calculated with samtools depth
\n\nThe output csv file will be saved in the \"BamDir_PATH\" directory with the name \"<sample>.mapstats.csv\""
}
}
```
